articles.author: Mari Yamaguchi
articles.title: Japan suspends 1.63M doses of Moderna over contamination - Associated Press
articles.description: TOKYO (AP) — Japan suspended use of about 1.63 million doses of Moderna vaccine Thursday after contamination was found in unused vials, raising concern of a supply shortage as the country tries to accelerate vaccinations amid a COVID-19 surge.
